SIMPLE: stertorous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stertorous
<hw>Ster"to*rous</hw> <pr>(st⟦etil⟧r"t⟦osl⟧*r⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>stertere</ets> to snore: cf. F.
<ets>stertoreux</ets>.]</ety> <def>Characterized by a deep snoring,
which accompanies inspiration in some diseases, especially apoplexy;
hence, hoarsely breathing; snoring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Burning, <qex>stertorous</qex> breath that hurt her cheek.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The day has ebbed away, and it is night in his room, before his
<qex>stertorous</qex> breathing lulls.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sterve</ent>⟦br⟧
